   <note>The label on the fore-edge section of the flap bears the rhyming title: “kalām Allāh al-qadīm wa’l-kitāb al-ʿaẓīm” (lit. an old copy of the word of God and the glorious book) its position reflects that in the Islamic lands books were shelved lying flat with their fore edge outward for preservation reasons it was impossible to photograph the complete binding.</note>
